{"parentUuid":"ae8b9526-415b-4992-8980-d4727a069e55","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a37d356d03020d6c4","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01DxxMhtEUmbznpUrQmtAhwy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01AD3aAgSCzdj311cvHUY6kR","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/devuser/Projects/cc-probeline/plans/tasks/phase-3-step3-review.md","old_string":"## REVIEW 2 — code-reviewer (sonnet, _pending_)\n\n(<redacted-i18n> <redacted-i18n> — Go quality, idioms, error wrapping, slog usage.)","new_string":"## REVIEW 2 — code-reviewer (sonnet, 2026-05-16)\n\n### Summary\n\n`detect.go` is well-structured, idiomatic Go: error wrapping is consistent,\ngodoc coverage is thorough, slog calls are properly structured key/value,\nand the function/type ordering matches the package conventions. The two\nnotable code-quality issues are: (1) `pickByMtime` computes and returns\n`time.Time` that the sole caller immediately discards — dead return value;\n(2) emoji comments in a shipped test file violate the project language-guard\nstyle rule. Remaining findings are minor (one redundant condition, one\nrepeated log call pattern).\n\n### Critical (must fix before close)\n\n<redacted-i18n>. (The non-absolute-path branch coverage gap is already C1 in REVIEW 1\nfrom a contract perspective; from Go quality perspective the error message\n`\"parser.detect: cwd must be absolute: %q\"` is informative and actionable —\nno additional code change needed in `detect.go` itself, only the missing\ntest.)\n\n### Important (should fix; orchestrator decides)\n\n**I-A. `pickByMtime` returns an unused `time.Time` value.**\n\n- File: `internal/parser/detect.go:189` — caller: `name, _, found := pickByMtime(entries, dir)`.\n  The mtime is computed and returned but discarded by the only caller.\n- From a Go idiom standpoint, returning a value that no caller uses is a\n  smell: it complicates the function signature and signals to future readers\n  that mtime is \"important\" when it is not actually consumed.\n- **Recommendation:** simplify the signature to `func pickByMtime(entries []fs.DirEntry, dir string) (string, bool)`.\n  If a future caller ever needs the mtime, it can re-stat the file.\n  This is a pure refactor with no behaviour change.\n\n**I-B. Emoji in shipped test file violates project style rule.**\n\n- File: `tests/parser/detect_test.go:585,589,594,599,604` — comments use\n  `✅` and `❌` glyphs.\n- Project CLAUDE.md and global instructions: «Avoid adding emojis to files\n  unless asked.» The `tests/` directory ships to the public mirror; the\n  language-guard blocks Cyrillic/CJK but emoji are not blocked there, so\n  these glyphs reach the public repo in violation of the style rule.\n- **Recommendation:** replace emoji with ASCII equivalents, e.g. `// [OK]`\n  and `// [ignored]`. One-line change per occurrence.\n\n**I-C. Log-capture soft-fallback silently disables assertions in two tests.**\n\n- Files: `tests/parser/detect_test.go:388-398` (`TestDetect_SessionIDMismatch`)\n  and `:558-567` (`TestDetect_TranscriptPathOutsideDir`).\n- Both tests capture slog output into a `bytes.Buffer` and then guard the\n  log assertion with `if logOutput == \"\" { t.Log(\"WARN: ... skipped\") }`.\n  In practice `slog.SetDefault` with a JSON handler over a `bytes.Buffer`\n  works correctly in Go's testing runtime, so the buffer should never be\n  empty. The soft-fallback makes the test appear to pass even if the log\n  message changes or disappears entirely — a hidden regression surface.\n- **Recommendation:** remove the `if logOutput == \"\"` soft-fallback.\n  If the buffer is empty unexpectedly, `t.Errorf` should fire on the\n  missing message assertion, not `t.Log`. The behaviour-only path can be\n  retained as a comment for documentation purposes.\n\n### Suggestions (nice-to-have; usually deferred)\n\n**S-A. Redundant `rel == \"..\"` condition in `validateTranscriptPath`.**\n\n- File: `internal/parser/detect.go:227`.\n- Condition: `strings.HasPrefix(rel, \"..\") || rel == \"..\"`. The second\n  operand is a strict subset of the first — `\"..\"` has prefix `\"..\"` by\n  definition. The redundancy is harmless but adds visual noise.\n- **Suggestion:** simplify to `strings.HasPrefix(rel, \"..\")`.\n\n**S-B. Repeated `slog.Info(\"parser.detect: resolved\", ...)` block appears 4× in `DetectActiveSession`.**\n\n- File: `internal/parser/detect.go:115-121`, `:136-143`, `:161-168`,\n  `:192-199`, `:203-210`.\n- Same 6-key log call copy-pasted with only `\"source\"` varying. Extracting\n  a small `logResolved(loc SessionLocation, source string)` helper would\n  reduce the repetition and make future field additions a single-site edit.\n- This is a style preference, not a correctness issue.\n\n**S-C. Per-test mtime assertions use `time.Now()` at table setup time, not per-subtable.**\n\n- File: `tests/parser/detect_test.go:271`, `:316` — `now := time.Now()` is\n  captured once per test function. This is correct; multi-second deltas\n  (`-3s`, `-2s`, `-1s`) used throughout make filesystem mtime resolution\n  irrelevant. No change needed; noted as explicitly good practice.\n\n### Code-style alignment with package\n\n`detect.go` feels native to the `parser` package. The godoc style matches\n`session.go` exactly (declarative voice, brief sentences, no marketing).\nError-prefix convention `\"parser.detect: ...\"` is consistent with the\npackage name and mirrors how `jsonl.go` would namespace errors if it had\nany. The one divergence: `jsonl.go` and `session.go` use no slog at all\n(pure computation), while `detect.go` is I/O-heavy and slog-heavy — but\nthat is appropriate to the function's nature, not a style inconsistency.\nslog key naming (`camelCase` for multi-word keys like `sessionID`,\n`transcriptPath`) is consistent within `detect.go` itself; since no other\nfile in the package uses slog, there is no package-level convention to\nviolate.\n\n### Approved for next step?\n\n**Yes-with-fixes** — Go quality is solid overall. I-A (simplify\n`pickByMtime` signature) and I-B (remove emoji from shipped test file) are\nthe highest-value fixes; I-C (harden log-capture assertions) is also\nrecommended before close."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1740,"cache_read_input_tokens":39056,"output_tokens":1744,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1740},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":1744,"cache_read_input_tokens":39056,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1740,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1740,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Cb5g2wPKT2xWF5kaLMXXr","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","type":"assistant","uuid":"e414be82-5ab8-4f80-b3cc-37b69614889a","timestamp":"2026-05-16T05:12:29.297Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"<redacted-45>","sessionId":"3067cc14-39c3-4ea9-b489-2a93f7621d10","version":"2.1.142","gitBranch":"<redacted-4>"}
